Results
Sequencing yields and optimal target base coverage

The targeted next-generation sequencing panel was designed to amplify all exons of the 12 known CMD associated genes ( Table 2 ). The overall target enrichment and next-generation sequencing yielded an average of 1,195,183 reads; 57% of these reads mapped to the genome and 35% mapped to the targeted regions. The total coverage of all targeted bases ranged from 87 to 94% at 5× and from 84 to 94% at 20×. The mean gene depth of coverage across all samples ranged from 0× for POMT1 to 108× for POMGNT1 , with an average of 50×. Despite the high mean gene read depth and target region coverage, several exons, including exon 1 of SEPN1 and all exons of POMT1 had no mapped reads [23] .
